23/10/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) â In an interview Saturday (October 21st) with the Sarajevo daily Dnevni avaz, EU Police Mission Commissioner Vincenzo Coppola said there should be no borders for police in BiH.
All policemen being free to do their job everywhere on Bosnian territory, he said, adding that even if the current entity interior ministries are preserved, command should be implemented at the state level.
Asked about Republika Srpska's opposition to police regions that cross inter-entity borders, Coppola said RS leaders should be aware that "police reform is the future for this country".
(Dnevni avaz - 21/10/06)
